def: A kind of large knife resembling a machete. [Phil. Islands]
Whereas.And flight and die is death destroying death; Where fearing dyingpays death servile breath. Shak.
A cross in the shape of the ankh.
The quality of being impressible; susceptibility.
Velvet. [Obs.] "A woman's crupper of velure." Shak.

A small insectivore (Centetes ecaudatus), native of Madagascar,but introduced also into the islands of Bourbon and Mauritius; --called also tanrec. The name is applied to other allied genera. SeeTendrac.
The act or process of cutting out a portion of the iris inorder to form an artificial pupil.
The quality of being demonstrable; demonstrability.
